\section{btable}

\texttt{btable} creates a simple barplot in a \LaTeX\ tabular. As an
example, add this to a Sweave file:
\begin{verbatim}
 \begin{tabular}{ll}
 <<echo=false, results=tex>>=
 x <- 1:5
 cat(btable(x, before = paste(1:5, "&"), after= "\\\\\n"))
 @ 
 \end{tabular}
\end{verbatim}

\noindent The output should be:

\begin{tabular}{ll}
<<echo=false, results=tex>>=
x <- 1:5
cat(btable(x, before = paste(1:5, "&"), after= "\\\\\n"))
@ 
\end{tabular}


